tool.name: buildMosiac

param.name: inMXD
param.dialogReference: A map document or folder that contains the rasters to insert into the mosaic dataset. Each raster must have auxiliary files that contain data that describe properties of the raster layer within the weighted overlay service.
param.pythonReference: A map document or folder that contains the rasters to insert into the mosaic dataset. Each raster must have auxiliary files that contain data that describe properties of the raster layer within the weighted overlay service.

param.name: in_worksapce
param.dialogReference: Path to the geodatabase that will contain the mosaic dataset.
param.pythonReference: Path to the geodatabase that will contain the mosaic dataset.

tool.summary: Creates a new mosaic dataset based on the output of the Feature to Raster, Optimize Raster, and Configure Raster Fields tools. This tool loads rasters within a map document or a folder into a new mosaic dataset. Data created by the Configure Raster Fields tool is inserted into rows within the mosaic dataset. Mosaic dataset properties, including default resampling method, are set.
